Pie Pie is a small shop with a large variety of v. good pizza. Standard cheese and pepperoni along with the current combo styles like 'salad pizza' ( c' mon, seriously? Salad pizza?) Call a head for pickup and it'll be ready by the time you get there. Or delivery, which is good too, but you should really get out in the fresh air for a few minutes, dontcha think? Anyway great pie, moderate price for the area.

"I could eat this until I die" -- My wife about this pizza.  Good prices, fast delivery, and a magically "just works" combination of flavors makes you think the pies are just MSG and cocaine.  Crust is of the medium thickness, soft and slightly chewy variety.  Tips:  1.) Order bacon as one of the toppings 2.) Order garlic knots and use them to sop up some of the initial grease on the pie. 3.) Be nice as their shop is very, very hot inside and they have a rough job.
